com.ostrichemulators.semtool.poi.main

Class XlsWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ostrichemulators.semtool.poi.main.XlsWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GraphWriter

    public class XlsWriter
extends Object
implements GraphWriter
    Create a workbook containing data formated in the Microsoft Excel Sheet Format. This class has two modes of operation: the ImportData mode, and the raw mode. In raw mode, callers should use createWorkbook(), createTab(java.lang.String), addRow(java.lang.String[]) and write(java.io.File) to generate the XLS file. In ImportData mode, just use the all-in-one function #write(gov.va.semoss.poi.main.ImportData, java.io.File) instead.

        public static String generateSheetName(String nodeKey,

        Common logic for finding a name for an excel workbook worksheet that is unique for that workbook and not longer than 32 characters. Each call to this function with the same nodeKey will generate a different name (Excel tabs cannot have identical names).

        keySet - Set of names that are already in use. the return of this function is automatically added to this set
